works.description: The beautiful and luxurious house of late four-times Oscar winner actress Katharine Hepburn is up for sale. The house, located in posh borough of Fenwick in Old Saybrook, was built by actress’ parents in 1913 for an expense of just $2,400, which is now on sale for whopping $ 28 million. The house got destroyed in 1938 during The Great New England Hurricane and was rebuilt by her parents. Hepburn stayed in this mansion till 2003, when she died at the age of 96. Substantial brick mansion was bought by Barbara and Frank Sciame, the chief executive of F.J. Sciame Construction
